{"/service/ndnp/vnstcsc/batch_vnstcsc_enighed_ver01/data/sn84037526/00414180012/1930041101/0336.xml":{"full_text":"{icean Dominion Steamship\nCorporation.\n5.9 \"Ll\nfrom New York is due at Frederiksted\nthis atternoon ang wiil be dispatchad for\nihe Leewaro and Windward Islands, ac\ncepling freight and passengers,\n#OB\u2019T. L. MERWIN CO, Inc\nAgents,\nPROFESSIONAL!\nIt is your interest to have YOUR EYES\n+Xxamined by ONE WHO KNOWS. Hav\ning twenty-five years experience in the\nPROFESSION it is no guess work. My\ninstallation o t\u00aee mmdern and up-to\ndiaie LENS Factory in the West Indies,\nputs me in a position to Supply Lenses\nfor the most Intricate iyes, apnd at\nprices to suit the pockets of all\nFram\u00abs of cvery deseription]stocked.\nMake Your Appoiniment A: Once!\nSHOR'IT STAY.\nPAKLOUR: 36 King Street Frederik\nsted.\nHours:; 10 a. m.to4 p. m.\nDR. J. R. MAYHEW,\nDr. Opt. Ref.\nLOCAL\nIhe Virgin Islands *\u2018Broadcaster\u2019\u2019 for\nApril 1,1930, is published and is being\ncirculatdd. As usual a copy hast been\nsent to this office It is filled with interest\ning reading, and contains about nine\nviews of pl@crs of interest of St. Thomas\n\u201c\u2018lsle of Enehaniing Views\u2019\u2019, but only\none view ot St, Croix, \u2018'Garden of the\nWest Indies\u2019\u2019\u201d. The \u2018\u2018Broadeaster\u2019 is\nprinted on a larger size paper this time,\n\u201c2We are glad to learn that the Educa\nsional Board of Review has received word\nin an official manner, that the High\nSchool question for St. Croix is getting\nthe careful sattention of His Excelleney\nGovernor Hvans, As to a place to be\nacquired, suitadble for teaching practieal\nagriculture, members of the Educaticnal\nBoard of Review have already given their\nopinion at the last meeting of the Board.\nThe foliowing is found in the \u2018\u2018Bullet\nin\u201d\u2019 of St. Thomas: \u2018\u2018Beginning with the\nfirst Monday after the 4th of July, a\nsummer School for teachers will be held\nin St. Thomas. !'hreecourses in educa\ntion, with college credit, will be given to\nteachers prepared todo advanced work.\nSubjects will be offered to those desiring\nto make up High Schoolg] credits.\nThese classes are organized primarily\nfor the benefit of the teachers,\nbut any adult is weicome to enroll,\nThose interested may obtain aa outline\nof the courses planned from the office of\nthe Director of Education.\u201d\u2019\nT 0 32\n\u201c*The Forbidden Woman,\u2019\u2019 the beauti\nful drama thet was {shown with success\nit the Christiansted Theatre on Sunday\nnighi, wiil be screened in Frederiksted\nTheatre tonight. \u2018\"Mockery\u2019\u2019 a splendid\nMetro-Goldwyn-Mayor production will be\nthe attraction at Bethlehem Theatre to\nnight.\nThere will be a Confirmation service in\nthe Lutheran Chureh in this sown on\nSunday April 13, (Palm funday) at 11 o\u2019\nclock a. m.\nEverybody seems to have their own\ntime nowadays. The town clock shcws\none time, the bells ring at ancther time,\nand the watches and clocks in different\nhomes and business places are pointing\nstill another ftime, Yesterday morniog\nsoms perscos regulated their !imepieces\nfrom the \u2018own clockjwhich showed a slow\ner time, only to find that by last night it\nwas changed again to a fasier time. We\nmust admit being puzzled and really do\nnot understand what is wrong.\nIt is reported that the pillars at the\nsouthern jend of the Public Grammar\nSchool gallery on the first floor, facing\nKing Street are in bad condition, and\nthat the teachers and pupi!s of the school\nare forbidden using the second and third\nfloor galleries for tear they may fall in.\nWe hzve always given a8 our opinion\nthat those old pillars were noi just right\nto support the new concrete work erected\nthere some years ago. It is hoped that\nthe repzirs will be effected there soon for\npubiic safety.\nThe plumbing wotk in the new soda\nwaler establishment of Mr. C. R. T.\nErow in King Street is being done by Mr.\nL. Scheen, who is a very capable man\nin the busines -of plumbing He is now\nepgaged in some fine work to the cis\nterns and inside the building.\nA large number of movie fans, in\ncluding some from Frederiksted attend\ned the moving picture show in the\nChristiansted Theatre last night, and\ne\u00a2verybody was well entertained with\nLon Chaney in \u2018\"Mockery\u201d and the\ntwo reel talking picture \u2018\u2018Men O\u2019 War\u201d\u2019\nwhich latter one was shown again\nby special request. No doubt folks\ntravelled all the way from Fred\neriksted to see \u2018\u2018Men O\u2019 War,\u201d\u2019\nas the talkies bid fair of becoming\nthe rage in ot. ;Croix. We are sure\nthat Frederiksted will get their talk\nies in time when everything is com\npleted, and according to the business\noutlook in the island in the future.\nWe learn that Director of Police Arm\nstrong is making ijpreparation to put the\nPolice stable yard in crack order, by\ngiving it a thorough cleaning out. That's\nright Direetor, have your yards beloning\nto the Police Department in fine eon\ndition.\nCENSUS NOTES.\nIn accordance with the proeclamation\nissued by the Governor of the Virgin [s\nlands, the census of the Virgic Islands\nof the United States to be taken asof\nthe first day of April, 1930, will begin on\nSaturday morning. the 12th day of April.\nThe enumeration will commence with\nthe enrollment of the Hon. R. W. Clark,\nDespatching Secretary, and his family.\nThe names of the enumerators are as\nfollows:\nChristionsted Town:\nMre. Elena Christian, Miss Medora\nJackson, Mr. Wilfred E. Messer.\nFrederiksted Town:\nMr. Amedec I Francis, Miss Ethanie\nSmith.\nCountry Districts:\nMr. Thomas J. Ash, Mr. Paul C. Chris\ntopher, Mr.D.Hamilton Jackson, Mr. Wil\nfrid James, M. Reginald McFarlane, Mr.\nHerman Sarauw.\nThe following questions with regard to\npopulation will be ask-d by the enumer\na(ors:\n1. Name?\n2 Relationship to head of the family?\n3. Whether home is 0w ned or rented.\n4. Whether home is free or mortgaged?\n5. Sex?\n6. Color or race?\n7. Age at last birthday?\n8 Marital condition?\n9. Whether attending school or college\nany time since Sept. 1, 19297\n10. Whether able to read end write?\n11. Where born?\n12 Where was father born?\n13. Where vas mcther born?\n14 What is yoor native language? (For\neign-born persons only.)\n15. What vear did you immigrate to the\nUnited States? (Foreign-bornj.\n16. Are you naturalized?\n17. Are you able to speak English?\n18. Your oecupsation?\n19. In what industry employed?\n20. Do you usually work at a gainful\noccupation?\n21. Are you now out of a job?\n22. If so, how many weeks have you\nbeen out of a job?\nROCEEDINGS\nOF THE\nCOLONIAL COUNCIL\nFOR ST. CRJIX.\n(Continued \u00a7from yesterday\u2019s Avis).\nIst Appointed Member (fFolden): Mr.\nChairman, have no reference to a com\nmunication which you as Chairman of the\nCouncil bave received; I was referripg to\na resolution sent to the Council\u2019s Com-","height":"18244","width":"15108"}}
